Freelander is a term for a person or group seeking political/personal freedom through [[emigration]] to and [[settlement]] of open land.  The term is primarily used in a fictional or speculative sense of freelanders emigrating from earth to other bodies in the [[solar system]].  Inherent to the idea of being a freelander is the idea of being independent and [[self-sufficient]].

Freelanders are typically described as associating with like-minded individuals, but different freelander groups may be quite different from one another (i.e., [[libertarian]] vs. [[authoritarian]], [[capitalist]] vs. [[communist]]).

Freelander: A model manufactured by the Land Rover company. A full time 4x4 off-road vehicle which saw the turn-around of fortunes that were eventually to save the marque. Originally part of Rover after the second world war, it became owned by BWM when they purchased Rover and then by Ford where it remains a part of their PAG (Premier Automotive Group) correct at March 2006. Full histories available elsewhere or by searching the various names..

